{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17531887","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17531887"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T16:20:09+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T16:20:09+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14636"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14636","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14636"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.31,0.13,0.1,0.16,0.3]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7329"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"57577"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7329","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7329"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14636"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"43036"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"28"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"1731"},{"type":"tags","id":"2295"},{"type":"tags","id":"2956"},{"type":"tags","id":"3136"},{"type":"tags","id":"3870"},{"type":"tags","id":"4032"},{"type":"tags","id":"4975"},{"type":"tags","id":"4979"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11639"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"17889"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43546"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"57577","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/57577"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 80-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with her daughter reporting severe leg discomfort and an irresistible urge to move her legs, particularly in the evenings and at night. These symptoms began two weeks ago and are significantly affecting her sleep. One month ago, she elected to cease haemodialysis and transition to comfort-focused care. She has end-stage renal disease secondary to diabetic nephropathy, type 2 diabetes, hypertension, and ischaemic heart disease. Her medications include insulin, metoprolol, and regular breakthrough oxycodone for chronic back pain. She lives in a residential aged care facility.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears comfortable at rest. Her pulse rate is 78/min, blood pressure 135/85 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 96% on room air, and temperature 36.7\u00b0C. There is bilateral pitting oedema to the mid-shin. Neurological examination reveals normal power and sensation in the lower limbs.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Iron supplementation","Compression stockings","Ropinirole","Pramipexole","Gabapentin"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has developed restless legs syndrome (RLS) after ceasing dialysis. While RLS is common in end-stage renal disease, management needs to be tailored to her palliative status and goals of care.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGabapentin\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate choice as it can effectively manage RLS symptoms with careful dose adjustment for renal function. While it requires monitoring for side effects, it offers a good balance between efficacy and safety in this context.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIron supplementation\u003C/strong\u003E may help RLS in patients with iron deficiency, but would not provide rapid symptom relief and is not aligned with the patient\u0027s comfort-focused goals of care.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECompression stockings\u003C/strong\u003E would be inappropriate and potentially harmful in this patient with significant peripheral oedema. They may increase discomfort and are difficult to apply in elderly patients.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPramipexole\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Eropinirole\u003C/strong\u003E are dopamine agonists that are effective for RLS but require careful titration and can cause significant side effects including orthostatic hypotension and confusion in elderly patients. They are not ideal in this palliative context where simplifying medication regimens is preferred.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther non-pharmacological measures that may help include gentle exercise during the day if possible, maintaining good sleep hygiene, and avoiding caffeine. The focus should be on maximising comfort and quality of life while minimising medication burden.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Gabapentin is effective for restless legs syndrome in patients with end-stage renal disease, with dose adjustment for renal function.","Non-pharmacological measures like massage and exercise remain important in palliative management of restless legs syndrome.","Quality of life symptoms should still be actively managed even when transitioning to comfort-focused care."],"references":["So S, Brennan FP, Li KC, Brown MA. End-stage kidney disease: The last 12 months. Aust J Gen Pract. 2021;50(4):193-198. doi:10.31128/AJGP-11-20-5736. Available online at ; https://www1.racgp.org.au/ajgp/2021/april/end-stage-kidney-disease-the-last-12-months-1","Huang CW, Lee MJ, Wang LJ, Lee PT, Tu YK, Hsu CW, Lin PY. Comparative efficacy and acceptability of treatments for restless legs syndrome in end-stage renal disease: a systematic review and network meta-analysis. Nephrology Dialysis Transplantation. 2020 Sep 1;35(9):1609-18. Available online at ; https://academic.oup.com/ndt/article/35/9/1609/5510127?login=false"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"43036"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14636"}},"stemMedia":{"data":